1
00:00:03,880 --> 00:00:04,840
Lak.

2
00:00:04,920 --> 00:00:06,560
Kluay said I'm going to die.

3
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:08,640
Lak, what did she say? Lak…

4
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:10,880
Lak, stop hanging out
with people like that already.

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:13,680
But this time she's serious, Sin.

6
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:17,200
<i>I'm scared, Sin. I don't want to die yet.</i>

7
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:24,840
- Lak!
- Sin!

8
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,040
Lak!

9
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:29,440
Lak!

10
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:31,560
Lak!

11
00:00:32,439 --> 00:00:35,000
Why is this happening, Lak…

12
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:40,320
Why did you kill my sister?!
Why did you kill her?!

13
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:42,600
- Sin!
- Why did you kill my sister?!

14
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:44,280
Get her! She killed my sister!

15
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:45,680
Why are you here, murderer?

16
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,880
- Why are you here?!
- Sin!

17
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,120
Why did you come here?!

18
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:24,400
Please take this document back
and review it for me.

19
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,960
See you.

20
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,560
So, Mr. Jirasin, how is it?

21
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,360
Has the money come in yet?

22
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,400
What money?

23
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,560
The share payment.

24
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,000
What shares?

25
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,480
The Vanich Mall shares
Mrs. Wanee gave you.

26
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,320
What do you mean?

27
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,400
- I came to say goodbye.
- Arnon.

28
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,600
Did you trick me into selling my shares?

29
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,880
- Hey, that's not fair.
- How is it not fair?

30
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,880
You sold them yourself.
Now that you've got the money,

31
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,040
you can't say that.

32
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,920
I'm declaring this share sale void.

33
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:58,880
You can't.

34
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,840
You tricked me into selling them.

35
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:02,080
Calm down, Jirasin.

36
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,360
You made the transaction yourself.

37
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,640
I have a legally valid signature.

38
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:10,320
And you signed it yourself.

39
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,600
I have CCTV evidence for everything.

40
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:16,360
So you're saying this whole thing…

41
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:20,560
Is a legal share transaction.

42
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:22,120
From now on,

43
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:25,000
you are no longer
a shareholder of Vanich Mall.

44
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,640
You planned all this, didn't you?

45
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:30,120
One day, Mrs. Wanee
will see what kind of person you are.

46
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:31,920
Go ahead.

47
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,000
I'm not afraid.

48
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:36,960
I think you should start packing now.
Because tomorrow,

49
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,400
Mr. Warat will fire you. Hit me.

50
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,160
Go on, hit me.

51
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:44,040
A few punches, why not?
You'll just get another charge added.

52
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,640
So how do you want me to help?

53
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,320
You broke up with Ameena.

54
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,880
And now Ameena is telling everyone
that she's pregnant with Warat's child.

55
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:07,240
But you know that's not true.

56
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,280
Then why would she do that?

57
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,360
Because everyone already knows

58
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:17,360
that Warat
is the new owner of Vanich Mall.

59
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:22,200
Do you really think
Ameena would think that simply?

60
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,280
This is a child's life.

61
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,760
It's not strange

62
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:30,640
that she'd rather build a family
with a billionaire heir

63
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:34,840
than with a poor architect like me.

64
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,400
What about the child?

65
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,000
Why don't you think
about the child's feelings?

66
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,600
How will they feel
when they find out one day

67
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,680
that man isn't their real father?

68
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,320
But maybe it's better for the child

69
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:52,720
to grow up surrounded by wealth,
instead of with a poor father like me.

70
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:55,440
I'm not Mr. Wichan's son.

71
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,560
Then whose son are you?

72
00:05:58,240 --> 00:06:00,680
It feels like
I've been lying to you this whole time.

73
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,600
But I…

74
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,920
I swear I never meant to.

75
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,200
That's not true, Det.

76
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,360
Something that's wrong

77
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,600
will always be wrong.

78
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:15,120
What right do you have to force a future
onto a child based on a lie?

79
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:18,360
You keep telling yourself
it will give them a better life,

80
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:19,800
a better future

81
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:23,080
when you already know it's not true.

82
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,680
So you're just
going to lie to them forever?

83
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,520
But it would give them a comfortable life.

84
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:31,760
Det,

85
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:35,800
that comfortable life you're talking about
is all in your imagination.

86
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,560
Why do you think that?

87
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,720
Because I've seen it before.

88
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:46,240
Giving your child to someone else

89
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,080
thinking their life will be better…

90
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:53,360
It doesn't make anyone happy.

91
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,840
- Hello.
<i>- Yes, Mr. Jirasin.</i>

92
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,160
Mr. Supol, I can't reach Mom.

93
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,280
Where is she?

94
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:09,960
<i>She's busy at the moment.</i>

95
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:12,920
I need to talk to her urgently.
Where is she?

96
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,160
<i>You'll have to wait until she's done.</i>

97
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,280
<i>I'll let her know to call you back.</i>

98
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,200
No, I can't wait.

99
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:22,040
This is urgent.

100
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,040
Well…

101
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:26,240
Mr. Supol, can you tell me where she is?

102
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,200
If she receives wrong information,
I'll be in trouble.

103
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,280
<i>But…</i>

104
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,000
Mr. Supol, please.

105
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,240
Please, just tell me where she is.

106
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:48,160
We've known each other
since Warat was a child.

107
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,400
It's a good thing

108
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,880
that our families
will finally be connected, isn't it?

109
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:55,880
Mm.

110
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,920
So, Warat,

111
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,960
which hotel do you want for the wedding?

112
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:07,560
Maybe we should let the kids decide.

113
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,520
Then we'll discuss it next time.

114
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,320
Warat, go check out some hotels.

115
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,400
I'll help you choose.

116
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:16,640
I have plenty of connections
in the hotel industry.

117
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:19,360
You can pick any style you like.

118
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:23,960
Alright?

119
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:29,760
Or maybe not in Bangkok?

120
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:30,920
Dad…

121
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,799
Can I talk to Warat
about the wedding myself?

122
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,159
Well, well.

123
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:40,280
I'm just happy that my daughter
is finally settling down.

124
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:41,960
Uncle, I…

125
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,320
Uncle what?

126
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,680
You can call me Dad. Don't be shy.

127
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,960
I'm not an heir of the Vanich family.

128
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:01,560
And I'm going to sign everything
back to Grandma.

129
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,040
What are you talking about?

130
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,160
I'm telling the truth.

131
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,720
I have no Vanich blood at all.

132
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,640
Then who are you?

133
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,480
I'm just someone
Grandma took in and raised.

134
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,800
I can never

135
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,440
repay her kindness in this lifetime.

136
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:32,640
After I return everything to her,

137
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:37,720
I'll spend
the rest of my life repaying her.

138
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,600
What about the child?

139
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,440
I have no wealth.

140
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,760
I'm not a Vanich heir.

141
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:03,880
I don't even know what my future will be.

142
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Well, I have an important appointment.

143
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,440
We'll talk about this later.

144
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:15,280
Do you still want Ameena to stay with me?

145
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:17,000
I need to go handle something first.

146
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,840
As for the details and responsibilities,

147
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,440
we can discuss them later.

148
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:23,920
Let's go.

149
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,640
Dad.

150
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,520
Can I talk to Warat for a moment?

151
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,680
Let's go home.

152
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:30,640
- But…
- I said let's go.

153
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:34,640
We might as well settle this now
and see what we can do.

154
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,600
What should I do about this?

155
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:05,880
<i>Who do you think Mrs. Wanee</i>
<i>will believe, you or Mr. Warat?</i>

156
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,760
And will she believe the evidence?

157
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,840
<i>- Good.</i>
- How is that good?

158
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:11,080
<i>If she believes evidence,</i>

159
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:13,840
<i>believes what's written,</i>
<i>then you just show her evidence.</i>

160
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,920
<i>- Are you Sin's assistant?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

161
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:21,480
<i>I need Sin's help.</i>

162
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,920
<i>What do you need?</i>

163
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,880
<i>I need the Vanich Mall shares</i>
<i>that Sin has.</i>

164
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:30,640
- And?
- You can say you sold them

165
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:31,960
because it was Mr. Golf,

166
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:34,320
part of the Vanich family.

167
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:36,800
And then?

168
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,520
<i>What actually happened is</i>

169
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,480
<i>it was Mr. Warat's plan</i>

170
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:42,000
<i>to ruin you.</i>

171
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,640
You're innocent.

172
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:47,280
You only did it
because you trusted Mr. Golf.

173
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:04,040
Ameena's father just left.

174
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,120
Why is he here?

175
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,600
Probably to talk to Mrs. Wanee

176
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:14,920
about Ameena's child.

177
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:20,040
But it doesn't look like it went well.

178
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:22,400
Warat probably won't accept the child.

179
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,720
Is Ameena here too?

180
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:29,000
She's still inside.

181
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,160
Well,

182
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:37,040
the reason you asked me to meet here
in the first place was because…

183
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,160
Yes.

184
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,040
I knew Ameena would be here.

185
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,560
Kluay, please help me.

186
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,520
I want you to tell everyone the truth.

187
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,200
I…

188
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,640
I want my family back.

189
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,480
Ameena.

190
00:12:57,160 --> 00:13:01,440
Tell me what really happened.

191
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:05,000
Tell me.

192
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,920
Let everything end at this table.

193
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,000
Just say it.

194
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,600
It's okay.

195
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,720
Well…

196
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,920
The baby is not Warat's.

197
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,640
Then why did you do this?

198
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,040
I…

199
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,200
I just…

200
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:43,200
So the baby is Det's, right?

201
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,840
But Det…

202
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:58,760
Weren't you afraid

203
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,160
you'd hurt him by doing this?

204
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,400
Det already broke up with me.

205
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,040
Why?

206
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,040
When I told him I was pregnant,

207
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:19,480
he said he didn't believe
the baby was his.

208
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:27,120
He said the baby was probably yours.

209
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,760
So you chose to do this?

210
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,160
I didn't want to do this.

211
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:37,080
Did your father tell you to?

212
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:54,880
Ameena,

213
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:56,920
listen to me.

214
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:00,000
Respecting your elders is good,

215
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:05,160
especially when that elder is your father.

216
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,440
But "elders,"

217
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:14,600
no matter how old they are,
are still human.

218
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,160
And humans

219
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:24,280
have greed, anger, and delusion.

220
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,360
Everyone has it.

221
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,040
From now on,

222
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:37,280
if he tells you to do something
that is wrong,

223
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,000
you must not do it.

224
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,800
And you must firmly refuse.

225
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,360
- Okay?
- Yes.

226
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,320
As for you,

227
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,360
you've grown into an adult now.

228
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:00,160
So from now on,

229
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:06,560
don't let anything bad

230
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:10,200
come and ruin your life again.

231
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:12,760
Okay?

232
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:18,040
I'm sorry, Grandma.

233
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,640
I'm really sorry.

234
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,640
It's okay.

235
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:25,640
I didn't want to do this.

236
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,880
It's alright.

237
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,280
I understand.

238
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:31,600
I understand.

239
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:35,960
It's okay. Let bygones

240
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,280
be bygones.

241
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,240
Ameena.

242
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:56,840
Kluay?

243
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:01,040
I asked her to come.

244
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:05,200
So that means…

245
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:09,119
Grandma and I already know the truth.

246
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:10,680
Warat…

247
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:16,040
What's done is done.

248
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:18,079
We can't undo it.

249
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:21,520
But it's not too late, Ameena,

250
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,839
to make things right.

251
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,040
But what is it?

252
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,640
Make what right?

253
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:30,800
Ameena.

254
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:34,440
I'm sorry.

255
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,120
Sorry for what?

256
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:49,920
We broke up, didn't we?

257
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,920
Why are you back?

258
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:56,560
I said those things out of anger.

259
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,040
Anger?

260
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:01,760
You always speak out of anger,
out of emotion.

261
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,480
Have you ever thought
about other people's feelings?

262
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:06,400
What you're saying isn't right either.

263
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,960
There's a limit to my patience.

264
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:09,080
Just stop talking.

265
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,200
I don't want to hear it.

266
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,240
If we've broken up, then go.

267
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:16,040
Why come back? Just go!

268
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:19,280
I've realized my mistake.

269
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:23,720
Realized?

270
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:29,000
Every time you mess up,
it's always the same.

271
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:30,080
Then what?

272
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:31,880
You do it again,

273
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:35,000
then say sorry, sorry, sorry.

274
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,040
But I've always given in to you.

275
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:38,560
Given in? How?

276
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,040
You want me to say it?

277
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,200
Then say it.

278
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,280
Det, calm down.

279
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,600
I have to say it.

280
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:49,920
I've kept this inside for so long.

281
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:54,000
If it's personal,
you two should talk privately.

282
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:56,920
It's not personal.

283
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,320
It's better if everyone hears this.

284
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,840
It's the truth I've been hiding.

285
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:09,680
Lakkana falling down the stairs
had nothing to do with Kluay at all.

286
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:14,840
What did you say?

287
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,360
- Sin?
- Sin.

288
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,040
I asked, what did you say?

289
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,400
I'm sorry, Sin.

290
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,520
Kluay what?

291
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,040
Well…

292
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,880
I asked, what did you say about Kluay?!

293
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,000
Well…

294
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:28,360
Kluay didn't push Lakkana down the stairs.

295
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:30,280
Then what Ameena said…

296
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:31,280
I'm sorry.

297
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,840
Why did you lie to me?

298
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:34,560
Have you been lying to me this whole time?

299
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:35,920
Sin.

300
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:36,960
Why did you lie?!

301
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,920
- Why did you do this? What is this?
- Stop.

302
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,320
I'm asking, what is this? What is this?!

303
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,240
Huh?

304
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,720
It's my fault, Sin.

305
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,120
I just didn't trust Det.

306
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,480
Didn't trust him how?

307
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:51,800
I didn't want him getting close to Kluay.

308
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,520
So you made everyone believe

309
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:58,560
that Kluay caused Lakkana's death?

310
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,400
I… I didn't think…

311
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:02,560
Didn't think what?!

312
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,280
This is someone's life.

313
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:08,000
- Uh!
- It's my sister's! Why did you do this?

314
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,320
Why did you do this?

315
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:11,360
- It's my sister's life!
- Sin.

316
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,280
Ouch!

317
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,320
- Hey, calm down.
- Damn it!

318
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,440
Stay out of this!

319
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,720
Stay out of this.
This doesn't concern you.

320
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:22,760
We'll need to talk later.

321
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:23,680
About what, Sin?

322
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,800
I'm sorry, Mom.

323
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:29,760
I…

324
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,760
Can I settle things about my sister first?

325
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,360
I'm really sorry.

326
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:37,200
This is important.

327
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:42,240
Are you going to tell me what it is?

328
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:43,840
What is it?

329
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,400
- Sin.
- I'm sorry.

330
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,800
I didn't want it to be like this.

331
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:50,440
You didn't want this?!

332
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,600
From now on,
let's pretend we never knew each other.

333
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,400
- Ouch!
- Sin, calm down.

334
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:03,240
Sin, I already apologized.

335
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,840
Calm down, bro.

336
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,000
You call me "bro"? You call me that?

337
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,320
Huh?!

338
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,280
You call me that?

339
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:14,680
But you lied to me. You lied to everyone!

340
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:15,680
Why?!

341
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:19,720
I… I just…

342
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:20,960
Just what?!

343
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,400
Just didn't tell the truth?

344
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,640
Just made everyone misunderstand?

345
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,360
Why did you do this?

346
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:32,440
- Why did you do this?
- Sin, let go.

347
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:34,400
Why did you do this?

348
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,080
- Sin.
- Why?!

349
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:37,240
Sin.

350
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:41,040
I…

351
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:44,520
Kluay.

352
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:45,960
I…

353
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,320
I'm sorry, Kluay. I understand now.

354
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,360
I…

355
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:55,360
I really cared about Lak.

356
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:58,720
I always did.

357
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,960
I know now. I was stupid.

358
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,600
I was stupid to believe these two.

359
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:09,200
I never thought my sister's death
would be used like this.

360
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:13,360
It's okay, Sin.

361
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,760
I just wanted to know…

362
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:21,240
have you forgiven me?

363
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,320
After all this time,

364
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:30,120
everything you did to me before

365
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:36,560
was just because you were angry, right?

366
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,400
Kluay, I…

367
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:48,000
I was wrong. I was stupid.

368
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:52,120
I was stupid to think…

369
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,640
you killed my sister.

370
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:58,640
And…

371
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,880
And you were living your life normally

372
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,280
while I…

373
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:05,880
I was drowning in my own pain.

374
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:10,880
Sin…

375
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:14,280
I'm sorry, Kluay. I understand now.

376
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:15,600
I know now that you…

377
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,080
you didn't

378
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:20,760
hurt Lak.

379
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,200
It's okay.

380
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:26,200
I've wanted us to understand each other
for a long time.

381
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:29,520
I'm sorry, Kluay.

382
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,760
- Sin, it's okay.
- I'm really sorry.

383
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:33,240
It's okay.

384
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:36,040
I never hated you.

385
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:42,200
I just wanted you to understand me.

386
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:48,480
Thank you, Kluay.

387
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:51,040
- Thank you.
- It's okay, Sin.

388
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:52,800
I'm sorry, Kluay.

389
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,360
For what I've done to you,

390
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:58,200
I'm sorry. I won't ever do that again.

391
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,680
I'm sorry, Kluay.

392
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,560
I'm really sorry.

393
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:06,800
Thank you, Sin.

394
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:19,120
I'm really sorry, Kluay.

395
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,320
Please.

396
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:54,840
Next time, you don't have to
open the car door for me.

397
00:24:57,560 --> 00:24:59,000
I've wanted to do it for a long time.

398
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:00,160
But…

399
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:02,280
But what?

400
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:05,920
I was worried about losing face.

401
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:11,480
Why would you lose face?

402
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:15,320
A man who takes care
of a woman like this is cute.

403
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:16,640
- Mm.
- But

404
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:19,160
next time, you don't have to do this.

405
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:21,600
Just be yourself.

406
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:23,600
Why?

407
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:27,640
Because if you do it today,

408
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,840
but later stop doing it,

409
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:35,000
I'll feel like you've changed.

410
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:36,120
Oh.

411
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:37,920
And…

412
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:40,120
if

413
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:43,760
one day I stop doing something,
you'll think I've changed?

414
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,440
If you really change,

415
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:51,160
I'll feel bad.

416
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:59,240
What about your ex?

417
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:02,440
Were you always consistent like this?

418
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:06,800
Well, I…

419
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:10,120
I…

420
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:13,920
- I…
- You what?

421
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,960
I've never had a girlfriend.

422
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:22,840
You're my first.

423
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:27,680
Huh? Me? Your first girlfriend?

424
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:29,960
I don't believe you.

425
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:31,400
Don't lie.

426
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:33,080
It's true.

427
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:38,960
In over 30 years,

428
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:42,200
you've never had a girlfriend

429
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:44,160
or dated anyone?

430
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:50,320
Well… I've been
taking care of Mr. Warat all the time.

431
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,880
When would I have time for a girlfriend?

432
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:55,520
Hm…

433
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:57,480
I've always thought that

434
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:58,720
one day,

435
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:03,560
I'd meet someone
who liked me, and I liked her too.

436
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:06,600
And when that happened,
I'd confess properly.

437
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:09,840
And the first person
I've ever confessed to

438
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:12,040
in my life is…

439
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:20,960
you

440
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:23,840
Mm.

441
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,360
Mm.

442
00:27:26,080 --> 00:27:27,480
Let's go.

443
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:30,400
You're holding my hand again.

444
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:34,680
It's hot today.

445
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,760
Mr. Warat,

446
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:48,200
about what Sin said earlier,
do you think he really meant it?

447
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:50,960
That apology just now?

448
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:56,400
You know what Jirasin is like.

449
00:27:58,160 --> 00:28:00,480
He did seem sincere though.

450
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:02,800
Like he really regrets it.

451
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:05,360
That's good.

452
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,320
But don't trust him too much.

453
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:10,120
Okay.

454
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:14,520
So what happened between you and him?

455
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:18,080
I did what I had to do

456
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:20,760
to protect Vanich.

457
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,320
Let's go.

458
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:34,880
I just realized that

459
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:39,720
holding hands with someone you love
feels this good.

460
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:41,840
Yeah, it does, but,

461
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:44,000
what if your mom sees us?

462
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:46,720
Hm, it's fine.

463
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:48,960
We're not doing anything wrong.

464
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:53,520
I know we're not doing anything wrong,
but if she sees, she might overthink it.

465
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:55,520
- No, she won't.
- Oh, come on.

466
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:59,360
I've known for a long time already
that you two like each other.

467
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:02,040
See? She knew.

468
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,560
Oh?

469
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:09,000
I don't mind.

470
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:11,120
If you two love each other,

471
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:14,200
as long as you stay
within proper boundaries

472
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:17,200
and don't bring us disgrace,
I won't say anything.

473
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:22,280
Yes. I understand
what's appropriate and what's not.

474
00:29:22,880 --> 00:29:24,480
Mm, good.

475
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:27,800
I believe you are mature enough.

476
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:30,520
Yes.

477
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:34,920
So, how are things with the other couple?

478
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:36,880
Not so good.

479
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:38,720
Oh? Why?

480
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:40,920
They seemed fine the other day.

481
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:41,880
Did they fight?

482
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:43,760
No, not exactly.

483
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:48,280
Arnon hasn't even told me about it yet.

484
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:55,880
I just don't know
what Mr. Warat is thinking.

485
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:10,760
Hello, Aunt Nong.
I need to talk to you about something.

486
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:14,240
<i>Sin, come home first. We'll talk then.</i>

487
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:15,800
<i>When are you coming back?</i>

488
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:17,880
Aunt Nong, Kluay…

489
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:20,040
<i>Kluay? What about her?</i>

490
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:22,880
She…

491
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:26,480
She's not the one who killed Lak.

492
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:28,760
<i>Even if she didn't kill Lakkana,</i>

493
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:32,240
<i>she still played a part in her death.</i>

494
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:35,800
I'm scared, Sin. I don't want to die.

495
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:39,360
<i>Think carefully, Sin.</i>
<i>What kind of normal person</i>

496
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:41,640
<i>would say someone is going to die?</i>

497
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:43,600
Yes.

498
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,480
<i>If Kluay hadn't said that,</i>

499
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:49,440
<i>Lak might still be alive.</i>

500
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:52,040
Yes, Aunt Nong.

501
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:55,240
<i>It's like a curse, Sin.</i>

502
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:58,720
Curse? Curse what?

503
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:00,680
<i>Kluay.</i>

504
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:03,200
<i>She cursed Lak to die.</i>

505
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,400
Who did this to you, Lak? Tell me.

506
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,080
Kluay said I'm going to die.

507
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:08,560
<i>Sin,</i>

508
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,480
<i>trust me.</i>

509
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:14,000
<i>I'm the one who cares about you the most.</i>

510
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:17,360
<i>The way you feel about Lak's death,</i>

511
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:19,200
<i>I feel the same.</i>

512
00:31:31,240 --> 00:31:34,360
With the utmost respect, ma'am,
what happened?

513
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,080
Ugh.

514
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:38,480
A lot of things.

515
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:42,440
Is there anything I can help with?

516
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:49,200
Well, it started with Ameena.

517
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,720
She suddenly claimed
she was pregnant with Warat's child.

518
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:55,640
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

519
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:58,000
if she really is pregnant,

520
00:31:58,080 --> 00:31:59,880
who is the father?

521
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:04,120
She confessed to me
that the child is actually Det's.

522
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:07,680
I see.

523
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:12,440
Ma'am, we're almost home.

524
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:15,120
After parking the car,

525
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:18,320
let's talk in my office.

526
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,200
Yes, ma'am.

527
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,960
So what do we do now?

528
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:43,760
I'm sorry.

529
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:47,040
What?

530
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:51,800
I'm sorry for being selfish.

531
00:32:53,560 --> 00:32:56,360
I'm sorry for always
assuming you'd give in.

532
00:33:02,320 --> 00:33:03,560
I'm sorry too,

533
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:06,160
for running away like that.

534
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,200
What's done is done.

535
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:17,800
We can't change the past.

536
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:23,040
I promise

537
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:26,400
I won't be selfish again.

538
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:29,000
I won't be unreasonable.

539
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:34,600
What about your father?

540
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:40,800
Doesn't he want you to marry Warat?

541
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:46,280
It doesn't matter anymore.

542
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,280
Now I know

543
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:53,840
who I should care about

544
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:56,960
the most.

545
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:03,560
If we know something is wrong

546
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:06,720
and we still choose to do it,

547
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,960
that means we chose

548
00:34:11,080 --> 00:34:12,400
to do the wrong thing.

549
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:17,760
But if we know it's wrong,

550
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:21,400
even if someone tells us to do it,

551
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,320
we must not do it.

552
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,320
I'm sorry

553
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:33,600
for being poor.

554
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,080
I'm sorry

555
00:34:37,159 --> 00:34:39,080
for having nothing.

556
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:42,679
I'm just a servant's son.

557
00:34:52,440 --> 00:34:53,960
It doesn't matter

558
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:56,719
who you are.

559
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:02,480
No one chooses where they're born.

560
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:05,840
At least,

561
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:08,680
you've tried your best

562
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,560
to make your life better.

563
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,280
And that's already enough.

564
00:35:17,720 --> 00:35:21,880
What you do matters more than who you are.

565
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,200
Why…

566
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:28,000
Now I know

567
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:32,320
how important you are to me.

568
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,720
Don't disappear again.

569
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:44,800
Don't walk away from me again.

570
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:50,560
We've been inseparable
for almost ten years.

571
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:52,800
I…

572
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:56,560
I can't imagine a life

573
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,240
without you.

574
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:04,080
Let's start over.

575
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,480
Let's build a family together.

576
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,600
Aunt Nong, I'm home.

577
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:57,440
Aunt Nong?

578
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:03,400
Uncle Rut.

579
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:05,160
Aunt Nong…

580
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:31,040
I…

581
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,840
I don't want to be a tool

582
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:35,920
in the Vanich family's
power struggle anymore.

583
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:38,280
<i>You're no longer useful to me.</i>

584
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:40,080
Let's break up.

585
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:41,440
NEXT EPISODE

586
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:44,840
<i>Kluay doesn't even know</i>
<i>who her parents are.</i>

587
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:46,760
Why would she care

588
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:50,360
whether Mr. Warat
is part of the Vanich family or not?

589
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:53,160
But the child in her womb is mine.

590
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:55,040
But I won't accept you.

591
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:56,840
Dad…

592
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,560
Ms. Ampha.

593
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:02,600
Where are you right now?

594
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:10,040
Ms. Ampha.

595
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:11,320
Ms. Ampha.

596
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:38,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
